       \n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"why-this-matters-now\"\u003eWhy this matters now\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eThe timing of this fix is particularly important given the economic landscape. With the Trump administration set to impose 25% tariffs on imported vehicles starting in April, car prices are likely to climb. That makes the $7,500 tax credit more valuable than ever for buyers looking to offset rising costs.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2025 Hyundai Ioniq 5 N\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8256\" height=\"5504\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODgzOTYy/large-57298-2025ioniq5n-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962-883962.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eFor many EV shoppers, this fix represents not just a financial reprieve but also a step toward making electric vehicles more accessible and affordable. However, it also highlights the need for smoother, more reliable government programs that don’t put consumers at risk of losing out on benefits due to paperwork delays.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-should-ev-buyers-do-now\"\u003eWhat should EV buyers do now?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eIf you bought an EV in 2024 and were denied the tax credit, reach out to your dealer as soon as possible. Since only dealers can access the IRS’s updated reporting system, they will need to submit the necessary information on your behalf. Don’t wait too long—the IRS has not indicated how long this fix will remain available.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eWhile this update is great news for EV buyers, it also serves as a reminder of the complexities of government incentives. Hopefully, future policies will be designed to prevent such issues from arising in the first place.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2025 Dodge Charger Daytona\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(min-width: 790px) 375px, (min-width: 768px) calc(50vw - 80px), calc(100vw - 24px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1NzQ3/DG025_041CH.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1NzQ3/DG025_041CH.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1NzQ3/DG025_041CH.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1NzQ3/DG025_041CH.jpg 64